24 SECTION 1. DO NOT CODIFY. Title.
25 This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Babies at Work Act".
26
27 SECTION 2. DO NOT CODIFY. Legislative findings and intent.
28 (a) The General Assembly finds that:
29 (1) A parent or guardian who is a public employee has a
30 responsibility to both his or her job and his or her family; and
31 (2) The first six (6) months of a child's life poses heightened
32 demands of a parent or a guardian.
33 (b) This act is intended to increase public employee retention by
34 allowing state agencies to permit a parent or guardian who is a public
35 employee to bring his or her infant to work.
